{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-fill-in-the-blank-show-tsx","path":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine/task-47","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"title":"Vežba 47","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Vrsta komande se koristi za davanje instrukcija, uputstava ili saveta. Pozitivna komanda obično počinje glagolom u osnovnom obliku, a negativna komanda počinje sa <span class=\"highlighted-text\">don't</span> ili <span class=\"highlighted-text\">do not</span>. Ovaj tip je uobičajen kada mu kažete nekome da nešto uradi ili ne uradi. Primer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Drink plenty of water.</span> — Ovde, glagol <span class=\"highlighted-text\">drink</span> daje savet o tome šta osoba treba da uradi.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Don't stay up too late.</span> — Ovde, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">don't</span> čini naredbu negativnom, govoreći nekome šta bi trebalo da izbegava da radi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>","instructions":"","explanation":null,"challengeType":22,"helpCategory":"English","superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","block":"learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine","lang":"en-US","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine/task-47"},"fillInTheBlank":{"sentence":"<p>BLANK one alarm and BLANK up when it rings.</p>","blanks":[{"answer":"Set","feedback":"<p>Ovaj glagol znači organizovati ili pripremiti nešto, kao što je podešavanje alarma. Prvo slovo je napisano velikim slovom.</p>"},{"answer":"get","feedback":"<p>Uz <span class=\"highlighted-text\">up</span>, ovaj glagol znači buditi se u krevetu.</p>"}]},"inputType":null,"tests":[],"transcript":null,"scene":{"setup":{"background":"interview-room1.png","characters":[{"character":"Expert","position":{"x":50,"y":15,"z":1.2},"opacity":0}],"audio":{"filename":"2.2-2.mp3","startTime